The paper deals with tensor factorization and completion, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Bayesian methods and probabilistic models also suggests a focus on statistical learning and inference. The applications of the method to image inpainting and facial image synthesis further suggest a connection to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of sparsity-inducing priors and hyperpriors also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
